subSubSection.paragraph:
Male
. Genitalia length 8.0 mm. Dorsal anterior margin of phallobase mesally concave (
Fig. 38
). Paramere ventral inner posterior margin inverted, elongate, spindle-shaped, and bounded by membranous integument; inner anterior margin elongate, spindle-shaped, apical outer margin widely carinate and sinuate, mid-posterior margin triangulate and rounded apically (
Fig. 39
). Dorsal anterior margin of the lateral processes and adjacent to the apical processes with V-shaped sclerites or processes. Dorsal mid-posterior margin short and bell-shaped, apical processes anterior angle narrow, apical anterior angle curved inwards. Paramere laterally with longitudinal groove on the mesal half, anterior to the dorsum and bounded by carinae on both sides; groove wider and parallel subapically, posteriorly, and mesally; posterior margin crescent-shaped and area towards the anterior margin immediate to the sub-apical groove widely curved (
Fig. 40
). Apical processes wider and lobe-like apically.
